data.enText: look/seem

before.enText: not used in the progressive tenses

data.enText: to give the impression of being or doing sth

data.chText: 她听到这消息时一点也没有显得吃惊。
data.enText: She didn't appear at all surprised at the news.

data.chText: 他看上去完全是个正常的人。
data.enText: He appears a perfectly normal person.
She appeared to be in her late thirties.

data.chText: 他们似乎不知道正在发生的事。
data.enText: They appeared not to know what was happening.
There appears to have been a mistake.
It appears that there has been a mistake.

data.chText: 看来利率不大会再降低。
data.enText: It appears unlikely that interest rates will fall further.
It would appear that this was a major problem.
be seen
to start to be seen

data.chText: 一辆公共汽车出现在拐角处。
data.enText: A bus appeared around the corner.
Smoke appeared on the horizon.
Three days later a rash appeared.
begin to exist
to begin to exist or be known or used for the first time

data.chText: 地球上的哺乳动物起源于何时？
data.enText: When did mammals appear on the earth?

data.chText: 这个问题最初在市区中心出现。
data.enText: This problem first appeared in the inner cities.
of book/programme
to be published or broadcast

data.chText: 他的新书将于春季出版。
data.enText: His new book will be appearing in the spring.

data.chText: 要阻止全国性报纸刊登这件事情已为时太晚。
data.enText: It was too late to prevent the story from appearing in the national newspapers.
in movie/play
to take part in a film/movie, play, television programme, etc.
He has appeared in over 60 movies.
She regularly appears on TV.

data.chText: 下月他将在百老汇上演的一出新戏中扮演布什。
data.enText: Next month he will be appearing as Bush in a new play on Broadway.
arrive
to arrive at a place

data.chText: 到十点钟李仍然没有露面。
data.enText: By ten o'clock Lee still hadn't appeared.
be written/mentioned
to be written or mentioned somewhere

data.chText: 你的名字将出现在书的前页。
data.enText: Your name will appear at the front of the book.
in court
to be present in court in order to give evidence or answer a charge

data.chText: 一个被控犯谋杀罪的男人今天将出庭受审。
data.enText: A man will appear in court today charged with the murder.

data.chText: 她因被控犯有六项盗窃罪而出庭受审。
data.enText: She appeared on six charges of theft.

data.chText: 明天他们将出庭接受地方法官的审讯。
data.enText: They will appear before magistrates tomorrow.

data.chText: 他已被传唤出庭为被告作证。
data.enText: He has been asked to appear as a witness for the defence.

data.chText: （作为律师）出庭；出庭当…的律师
data.enText: to act as sb's lawyer in court

data.chText: 谢丽∙布思作为被告的辩护律师出庭。
data.enText: Cherie Booth is the lawyer appearing for the defendant.

simple_means.memory_skill: ap 表加强 + pear 看见 → 看见 → 出现

ex.chText: 一艘军舰出现在港口附近。
ex.enText: A warship appeared near the harbour.

ex.chText: 她在舞台上亮相。
ex.enText: She appeared on the stage.

ex.chText: 她曾上过全国性电视节目。
ex.enText: She appeared on national television.

synonyms.bx: 强调进入视野为人所见，也指公开露面为公众所看见。

ex.chText: 他工作中出现了困难。
ex.enText: Difficulties arose in his work.

ex.chText: 外交部出现了危机。
ex.enText: A crisis has arisen in the Foreign Office.

ex.chText: 太阳从云层后面露出来了。
ex.enText: The sun emerged from behind the clouds.

ex.chText: 一艘潜艇浮出海面。
ex.enText: A submarine emerged from the sea.

ex.chText: 我们探讨得再深入一点就发现，问题开始出现了。
ex.enText: When we look a bit deeper, problems begin to emerge.

synonyms.bx: 指从某个掩蔽处出现或摆脱遮挡物而被看见，强调缓缓出现的过程，常后接介词 from。

ex.chText: 雾中隐隐现出一艘小船。
ex.enText: A boat loomed out of the fog.

ex.chText: 一座岛屿赫然出现在地平线上。
ex.enText: An island loomed on the horizon.

synonyms.bx: 尤指轮廓不清、令人惊恐地隐现。

ex.chText: 她的眼神显露出忧愁。
ex.enText: Her worry showed in her eyes.

ex.chText: 西班牙的经济开始显露出复苏的迹象。
ex.enText: Spain's economy began to show signs of recovery.

synonyms.bx: 语气较强，强调明显地表现出来。

ex.chText: 他看上去脸色苍白。
ex.enText: He looks pale.

ex.chText: 他看上去像个大夫。
ex.enText: He looks like a doctor.

ex.chText: 他看上去好像一星期没有睡觉了。
ex.enText: He looked/seemed as if he hadn't slept for a week.

synonyms.bx: 侧重由视觉得出某种印象，后接 as if 引导的表语从句时常可与 seem 换用。

ex.chText: 他看起来不高兴。
ex.enText: He appears/seems unhappy.

ex.chText: 警方称似乎有破门而入的迹象。
ex.enText: Police said that there appeared/seemed to be signs of a break-in.

ex.chText: 似乎是他杀了这个男人。
ex.enText: It appears/seems that he killed the man.

synonyms.bx: 尤指从所知或所见得到某种印象，常后接动词不定式或 that 引导的表语从句，常可与 seem 换用。

ex.chText: 天好像要下雨。
ex.enText: It seems like it's going to rain.

ex.chText: 我们教练似乎是一个精力充沛的人。
ex.enText: Our coach seems like an energetic person.

ex.chText: 孩子们在情绪上似乎并未受到父母离婚的影响。
ex.enText: The kids seem unaffected emotionally by their parents' divorce.

synonyms.bx: 侧重指由主观看法得出判断，但暗示有一定的依据。

example: He suddenly appeared at the wedding
A new star appeared on the horizon

tr: come into being or existence, or appear on the scene
example: Then the computer came along and changed our lives
Homo sapiens appeared millions of years ago
Did your latest book appear yet?
The new Woody Allen film hasn't come out yet

tr: appear as a character on stage or appear in a play, etc.
example: Gielgud appears briefly in this movie
She appeared in `Hamlet' on the London stage

tr: give a certain impression or have a certain outward aspect
example: This appears to be a very difficult problem
They appeared like people who had not eaten or slept for a long time

tr: seem to be true, probable, or apparent
example: It seems that he is very gifted
It appears that the weather in California is very bad

tr: present oneself formally, as before a (judicial) authority
example: He had to appear in court last month
She appeared on several charges of theft

value.def: If you say that something appears to be the way you describe it, you are reporting what you believe or what you have been told, though you cannot be sure it is true.

example.ex: There appears to be increasing support for the leadership to take a more aggressive stance...
example.tran: 好像有越来越多的人支持领导层采取更为强势的立场。

example.ex: The aircraft appears to have crashed near Katmandu...
example.tran: 飞机似乎在加德满都附近坠毁了。

example.ex: It appears that some missiles have been moved...
example.tran: 一些导弹似乎已经被移走了。

example.ex: It appears unlikely that the UN would consider making such a move...
example.tran: 看起来联合国不太可能考虑采取这样一种行动。

example.ex: The presidency is beginning to appear a political irrelevance...
example.tran: 总统一职似乎正在沦为政治上的摆设。

example.ex: Nine months later, those talks appear as distant as ever...
example.tran: 9个月以后，那些会谈似乎仍然遥遥无期。

example.ex: He appeared willing to reach an agreement.
example.tran: 他似乎愿意达成协议。

value.def: If someone or something appears to have a particular quality or characteristic, they give the impression of having that quality or characteristic.

example.ex: She did her best to appear more self-assured than she felt...
example.tran: 她竭力让自己表现得比实际更自信。

example.ex: He is anxious to appear a gentleman...
example.tran: 他急于想表现得像个绅士。

example.ex: Under stress these people will appear to be superficial, over-eager and manipulative.
example.tran: 这些人在压力下会显得浅薄无知、操之过急，而且爱摆布人。

value.def: When someone or something appears, they move into a position where you can see them.

example.ex: A woman appeared at the far end of the street...
example.tran: 一个女人远远出现在街的尽头。

example.ex: Last night some of the prisoners appeared on the roof.
example.tran: 昨晚，其中几个犯人出现在房顶上。

value.def: When something new appears, it begins to exist or reaches a stage of development where its existence can be noticed.

example.ex: ...small white flowers which appear in early summer...
example.tran: 初夏时绽放的白色小花

example.ex: Slogans have appeared on walls around the city.
example.tran: 标语已出现在全城周围的墙上。

example.ex: ...a test which can reveal infection at an early stage, before symptoms appear...
example.tran: 可在症状出现前检测出早期感染的测试

value.def: When something such as a book appears, it is published or becomes available for people to buy.

example.ex: I could hardly wait for 'Boys' World' to appear each month.
example.tran: 每个月我都翘首期盼着《男孩世界》的出版。

example.ex: ...a poem which appeared in his last collection of verse.
example.tran: 发表在他最后一部诗集中的一首诗

value.def: When someone appears in something such as a play, a show, or a television programme, they take part in it.

example.ex: Jill Bennett became John Osborne's fourth wife, and appeared in several of his plays...
example.tran: 吉尔·本内特成为了约翰·奥斯本的第四任妻子，并参演过他的几部戏剧。

example.ex: Student leaders appeared on television to ask for calm.
example.tran: 学生领袖出现在电视上请求大家保持冷静。

value.def: When someone appears before a court of law or before an official committee, they go there in order to answer charges or to give information as a witness.

example.ex: Two other executives appeared at Worthing Magistrates' Court charged with tax fraud...
example.tran: 又有两个经理因偷税漏税指控被传唤到沃辛治安法庭。

example.ex: The American will appear before members of the disciplinary committee at Portman Square.
example.tran: 那个美国人将在波特曼广场接受纪律委员会成员的审问。

trans: 似乎是；似乎有；看来；仿佛；似乎
显示脱机；隐身；显示为离线

rootsaffixes.indicate: = to come in sight 看见
rootsaffixes.title: pear

partsOfSpeech.dec: ap 表加强 + pear 看见 → 看见 → 出现
appear 出现 + ance 状态，性质，状况 → 出现
dis 不 + appear 出现 → 不出现 → 消失
re 重新 + appear 出现 → 再现
